From: Loicque WINDEY <loicque.windey@hsbcpb.com>
Date: Fri, 1 Nov 2019 at 12:26
Subject: Follow up on fee discussion
To: Adam Marash <adam@marash.net>, Tamar Marash <tamar@marash.net>
Cc: ANNERIEN HURTER <annerien.hurter@hsbcpb.com>, Craig WARREN <
craig.warren@hsbc.com>, STEPHANIE RITSON <stephanie.ritson@hsbcpb.com>


Dear Tamar and Adam



Thank you for your time on the phone earlier today.



As discussed, having a Guernsey account tends to come with a higher cost to
the client (and the bank).

Also, as opposed to brokers we offer our clients a full-service approach,
including financial planning services etc.

We also have a very high credit rating safeguarding your assets which is an
element to consider.



As we do value your business, we are happy to initiate the discount process
for your accounts with us.

We hope to come to a mutually acceptable outcome enabling us to have a long
term fruitful relationship.



As discussed, we propose to reduce your commissions to the following
schedule:





*Fixed Income*

*Equity*

Up to GBP 250k

0.35%

0.40%

GBP 250k-500k

0.30%

0.35%

Above GBP 500k

0.20%

0.25%



Our standard *custody*/account fee is 25bps , however we are happy to
reduce this to 15bps for you.



From speaking to the portfolio managers, we are under the impression that
the investment strategies are mostly buy and hold.

We therefore would not anticipate much trading once the portfolio is fully
invested. A reduced custody fee should therefore have a significant impact.



Should our understanding be incorrect, please could you kindly provide us
with accurate expectations in terms of trading volume and turnover.

If the accounts would prove to be trading very actively, then I can try to
make a better case to our fee approval team.



Take your time to review these fees with Eran and Richard, and feel free to
get back with any questions.

We are happy to have a call with them as well, and note also that Annerien
will be in Tel Aviv meeting them during our Investment Outlook later this
month.



Kind regards

Loicque

